    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Books having leaves that are relatively rigid, and that may be in non-traditional forms. Often used to refer to board books or books whose leaves are glued together as part of the binding process, though the concept of board books is distinct.</Note_Text>
